nk, cleanse, and preen, flicking their tails sideways and chattering incessantly. Pairs build a domed nest from grasses, lined with fine grass, feathers, and charcoal, in the late wet or early dry season. The nest position varies: it can be as high as 20 metres or simply hidden in long grass. Five to six white eggs are laid. References BirdLife International (2008) Species factsheet: Poephila personata. Downloaded from http://www.birdlife.org on 5 August 2008. Clement, Peter; Harris, Alan & Davies, John (1993) Finches and Sparrows: An Identification Guide, Christopher Helm, London. Pizzey, Graham & Knight, Frank (1997) Birds of Australia, HarperCollins, London.", "shortSummary": "The masked finch (Poephila personata) is a small passerine bird in the estrildid finch family, Estrildidae. It is a common resident of dry…", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1a/Masked_Finch_7355-2.jpg/960px-Masked_Finch_7355-2.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-poephila", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-poephila-personata", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-poephila", "species": "taxonomy-species-poephila-personata"}, "expandable": true, "x": -395.55, "y": 47.33, "z": -299.1}], "links": [{"key": "bird-masked-finch-08002907__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-poephila-personata", "source": "bird-masked-finch-08002907", "target": "taxonomy-species-poephila-personata", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-poephila-personata__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-poephila", "source": "taxonomy-species-poephila-personata", "target": "taxonomy-genus-poephila", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Masked finch 属于属 Poephi